Process called "create_default_widget_style" that takes widget_type as WidgetType returns WidgetStyle:
    Note: Create default style for widget type
    Return WidgetStyle with:
        background_color as Color with red as 255 and green as 255 and blue as 255 and alpha as 255
        foreground_color as Color with red as 0 and green as 0 and blue as 0 and alpha as 255
        border_color as Color with red as 128 and green as 128 and blue as 128 and alpha as 255
        border_width as 1
        border_radius as 0
        font as create_default_font
        padding as Padding with top as 5 and right as 5 and bottom as 5 and left as 5
        margin as Margins with top as 2 and right as 2 and bottom as 2 and left as 2
        opacity as 1.0
        shadow as none
        animation as none
        custom_properties as empty dictionary

